{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-23T13:49:28.968Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":1},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets in Python — A Complete Guide for AI & Data Science"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"set"},{"type":"text","text":" is an unordered collection of unique elements. Unlike lists or arrays, a set automatically removes duplicates and does not preserve insertion order. It is one of Python's four core built-in collection types, and it maps closely to the mathematical concept of a set — making it especially powerful for operations like union, intersection, and difference."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Python, a set is defined using curly braces "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{}"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"set()"},{"type":"text","text":" constructor:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"fruits = {\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\"}\nempty_set = set()  # NOT {} — that creates an empty dict"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each element in a set must be "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" (immutable). This means you can store strings, numbers, and tuples in a set, but not lists or dictionaries."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets are part of Python's built-in data model, backed by a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hash table"},{"type":"text","text":" internally — the same underlying mechanism as Python dictionaries. This is why membership tests ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"in"},{"type":"text","text":") are extremely fast."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets solve a fundamental class of problems:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Uniqueness enforcement"},{"type":"text","text":" — automatically deduplicate data without writing loops"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fast membership testing"},{"type":"text","text":" — checking whether something exists is O(1), compared to O(n) for a list"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Relational operations"},{"type":"text","text":" — union, intersection, difference, and symmetric difference mirror real mathematical reasoning"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In Generative AI and data pipelines, these properties are used constantly:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deduplicating tokenized vocabulary"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Checking feature overlap between datasets"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Filtering out seen items in recommendation engines"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set-based logic in knowledge graph traversal"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"O(1) average-case lookup"},{"type":"text","text":" — regardless of set size, checking membership is nearly instant"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Automatic deduplication"},{"type":"text","text":" — inserting an existing element simply does nothing; no extra code needed"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematical set operations"},{"type":"text","text":" built into the language"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Memory-efficient for uniqueness checks"},{"type":"text","text":" — cleaner than maintaining a list and manually checking "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"if x not in list"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Readable code"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"A & B"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"A | B"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"A - B"},{"type":"text","text":" are immediately meaningful to anyone who knows set theory"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Unordered"},{"type":"text","text":" — there is no concept of first or last element; you cannot index into a set with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"set"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No duplicates"},{"type":"text","text":" — if count matters (e.g., word frequency), a set is the wrong tool; use a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Counter"},{"type":"text","text":" or dictionary"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Elements must be hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" — lists, dicts, and other mutable types cannot be stored in a set"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No slicing"},{"type":"text","text":" — since sets have no order, slicing is undefined"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Slightly higher memory overhead"},{"type":"text","text":" than a list for small collections, due to the hash table structure"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Internally, Python sets are implemented as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hash tables"},{"type":"text","text":". Here is what happens step by step when you add an element:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Python computes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"hash(element)"},{"type":"text","text":" — a fixed-size integer fingerprint of the value"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That hash determines a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"slot"},{"type":"text","text":" (bucket) in the hash table"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The element is stored in that slot"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When checking "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x in my_set"},{"type":"text","text":", Python computes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"hash(x)"},{"type":"text","text":" again and checks just that slot — no scanning needed"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is why:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Lookup is O(1) average (O(n) worst case due to hash collisions, but rare in practice)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Only hashable (immutable) types can be elements — mutable types would change their hash after insertion, breaking the structure"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Hash example\nprint(hash(\"apple\"))   # e.g., 3713081631934410656\nprint(hash(42))        # 42\nprint(hash((1, 2)))    # some integer\n# hash([1, 2])         # TypeError: unhashable type: 'list'"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture / Flow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a conceptual view of how set operations work in memory:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set A = {1, 2, 3, 4}         Set B = {3, 4, 5, 6}\n\nHash Table A:                 Hash Table B:\n[ slot: 1 ]                  [ slot: 3 ]\n[ slot: 2 ]                  [ slot: 4 ]\n[ slot: 3 ]                  [ slot: 5 ]\n[ slot: 4 ]                  [ slot: 6 ]\n\nA | B  (union)       → {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}   — all slots from both\nA & B  (intersection)→ {3, 4}               — slots present in both\nA - B  (difference)  → {1, 2}               — slots in A not in B\nA ^ B  (sym. diff.)  → {1, 2, 5, 6}         — slots in exactly one"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each operation iterates over one or both hash tables and builds a new one — so set operations are O(min(len(A), len(B))) to O(len(A) + len(B)) depending on the operation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use It"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use a set when:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Uniqueness of elements is the primary concern"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fast membership testing is needed ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x in collection"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to perform union, intersection, or difference operations"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deduplicating an existing list or sequence"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Do not use a set when:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Order matters (use a list or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"collections.OrderedDict"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Duplicate counts matter (use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"collections.Counter"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to access elements by index (use a list or tuple)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Elements are mutable (use a list)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You want a fixed, immutable set — use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"frozenset"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Implement"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating Sets"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# From a literal\ncolors = {\"red\", \"green\", \"blue\"}\n\n# From a list (deduplicates automatically)\nnums = set([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3])   # {1, 2, 3}\n\n# Empty set — must use set(), not {}\nempty = set()\n\n# Set comprehension\nsquares = {x**2 for x in range(10)}   # {0, 1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81}"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adding and Removing Elements"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"s = {\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"}\n\ns.add(\"d\")          # adds one element\ns.update([\"e\", \"f\"])  # adds multiple elements\n\ns.remove(\"a\")       # raises KeyError if not found\ns.discard(\"z\")      # safe — does nothing if not found\n\npopped = s.pop()    # removes and returns an arbitrary element\ns.clear()           # empties the set"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Membership Testing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"vocab = {\"the\", \"a\", \"is\", \"are\"}\n\nprint(\"the\" in vocab)    # True — O(1)\nprint(\"robot\" in vocab)  # False — O(1)\nprint(\"a\" not in vocab)  # False"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set Operations"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"A = {1, 2, 3, 4}\nB = {3, 4, 5, 6}\n\n# Union — all elements from both\nprint(A | B)          # {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}\nprint(A.union(B))     # same\n\n# Intersection — only elements in both\nprint(A & B)          # {3, 4}\nprint(A.intersection(B))\n\n# Difference — in A but not B\nprint(A - B)          # {1, 2}\nprint(A.difference(B))\n\n# Symmetric difference — in either but not both\nprint(A ^ B)          # {1, 2, 5, 6}\nprint(A.symmetric_difference(B))\n\n# Subset / superset\nprint({1, 2}.issubset(A))    # True\nprint(A.issuperset({1, 2}))  # True\nprint(A.isdisjoint({7, 8}))  # True — no elements in common"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Frozenset — Immutable Sets"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"fs = frozenset([1, 2, 3])\n# fs.add(4)   # AttributeError — frozensets are immutable\n\n# Useful as dict keys or elements of another set\nd = {frozenset([1, 2]): \"pair\"}\nnested = {frozenset({1, 2}), frozenset({3, 4})}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1 — Deduplicate a List"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"raw_tokens = [\"the\", \"cat\", \"sat\", \"the\", \"cat\"]\nunique_tokens = set(raw_tokens)\nprint(unique_tokens)   # {\"the\", \"cat\", \"sat\"}"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 2 — Fast Tag Lookup"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"stop_words = {\"the\", \"a\", \"an\", \"is\", \"are\", \"was\"}\n\ndef is_stop_word(word):\n    return word in stop_words   # O(1)\n\nprint(is_stop_word(\"the\"))    # True\nprint(is_stop_word(\"robot\"))  # False"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 3 — Finding Common Features"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"model_A_features = {\"age\", \"income\", \"location\", \"device\"}\nmodel_B_features = {\"income\", \"device\", \"clicks\", \"sessions\"}\n\nshared = model_A_features & model_B_features\nprint(shared)   # {\"income\", \"device\"}\n\nonly_in_A = model_A_features - model_B_features\nprint(only_in_A)   # {\"age\", \"location\"}"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 4 — Set Comprehension with Filtering"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"words = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"apricot\", \"cherry\", \"avocado\"]\na_words = {w for w in words if w.startswith(\"a\")}\nprint(a_words)   # {\"apple\", \"apricot\", \"avocado\"}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Example — Building a Vocabulary for an NLP Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In a real tokenization pipeline for a language model, you might process millions of text samples and need to:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Collect all unique tokens across the corpus"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Remove tokens already seen in the base vocabulary"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Identify tokens shared between training and validation sets (to detect leakage)"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"from collections import Counter\n\n# Simulated corpus\ntrain_tokens = [\"the\", \"cat\", \"sat\", \"on\", \"the\", \"mat\", \"cat\"]\nval_tokens   = [\"the\", \"dog\", \"sat\", \"on\", \"the\", \"floor\"]\n\n# Unique vocabularies\ntrain_vocab = set(train_tokens)   # {\"the\", \"cat\", \"sat\", \"on\", \"mat\"}\nval_vocab   = set(val_tokens)     # {\"the\", \"dog\", \"sat\", \"on\", \"floor\"}\n\n# Overlap check — tokens seen in both splits\noverlap = train_vocab & val_vocab\nprint(\"Shared tokens:\", overlap)   # {\"the\", \"sat\", \"on\"}\n\n# Tokens only in validation (OOV — out of vocabulary)\noov = val_vocab - train_vocab\nprint(\"OOV tokens:\", oov)   # {\"dog\", \"floor\"}\n\n# Full vocabulary for tokenizer\nfull_vocab = train_vocab | val_vocab\nprint(\"Full vocab size:\", len(full_vocab))   # 7\n\n# Base vocabulary to exclude (e.g., existing tokenizer vocab)\nbase_vocab = {\"the\", \"on\", \"is\", \"a\"}\nnew_tokens = full_vocab - base_vocab\nprint(\"New tokens to add:\", new_tokens)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"At scale — say 100 million tokens — sets remain efficient because all operations remain O(n) in the worst case and the hash-table structure avoids any element-by-element list scanning."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"{}"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" to create an empty set"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"empty = {}      # This is a dict, not a set!\nempty = set()   # Correct"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Trying to index a set"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"s = {10, 20, 30}\nprint(s[0])   # TypeError: 'set' object is not subscriptable\n# Convert to list first if indexing is needed\nprint(list(s)[0])"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Storing mutable elements"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"s = set()\ns.add([1, 2, 3])   # TypeError: unhashable type: 'list'\ns.add((1, 2, 3))   # OK — tuples are hashable"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Expecting a consistent order"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"s = {3, 1, 2}\nprint(s)   # Could print {1, 2, 3} or {3, 1, 2} — order is undefined\n# Never rely on set ordering in logic or assertions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Using a set when counts matter"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"words = [\"the\", \"the\", \"cat\"]\nword_set = set(words)    # {\"the\", \"cat\"} — frequency information lost\n# Use Counter instead:\nfrom collections import Counter\ncounts = Counter(words)   # {\"the\": 2, \"cat\": 1}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Modifying a set while iterating"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"s = {1, 2, 3, 4}\nfor x in s:\n    s.discard(x)   # RuntimeError: Set changed size during iteration\n# Iterate over a copy instead:\nfor x in set(s):\n    s.discard(x)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefer sets over lists for membership tests"},{"type":"text","text":" when the collection is large — switching from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x in list"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"x in set"},{"type":"text","text":" can cut lookup time from milliseconds to microseconds at scale"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convert to frozenset when immutability is needed"},{"type":"text","text":" — e.g., as dictionary keys or as safe constants that should not change"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use set comprehensions"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of building a list and converting — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{expr for x in iterable}"},{"type":"text","text":" is both faster and more readable"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":".discard()"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" instead of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":".remove()"},{"type":"text","text":" in defensive code where the element might not exist"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combine with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"Counter"},{"type":"text","text":" when both uniqueness and frequency are relevant — get the set from "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"counter.keys()"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Name sets clearly"},{"type":"text","text":" — use names like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"seen_ids"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"stop_words"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"valid_tags"},{"type":"text","text":" that communicate the uniqueness intent"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"isdisjoint()"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" for mutual exclusion checks"},{"type":"text","text":" — more readable than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"len(A & B) == 0"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance & Scalability"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"col